{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"8ae178de-1756-4d44-9f1e-b656bb78bdac","content":"The directory doesn't exist yet, but I can tell you exactly what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish a C# MCP server as a **dotnet tool** on NuGet.org:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Mark as a dotnet tool -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <!-- Command users will run (e.g., `dotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer` then `my-mcp-server`) -->\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- Must be Exe for stdio transport -->\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</RepositoryUrl>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Publish steps\n\n```bash\n# 1. Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# 2. Push to NuGet.org (requires an API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run it\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server          # runs via stdio\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `PackAsTool` + `ToolCommandName` are the critical properties — they tell `dotnet pack` to produce a tool package.\n- `OutputType` must be `Exe` (required for stdio transport).\n- Optional: set `<RollForward>Major</RollForward>` for broader .NET runtime compatibility.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b56f6a16-b50e-4467-aa00-5991fd1be04f","outputTokens":542,"requestId":"3840:1FB426:7006499:7868FEF:6A03D02C"},"id":"f4f8c57a-7541-434b-b40c-b90f872d0ae1","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:13:27.770Z","parentId":"585d06af-1236-4b0b-8810-ee0